The paper deals with the problem of estimating the parameters of a one-layer ReLU neural network that generates a rectified Gaussian distribution. This problem falls under the domain of machine learning and specifically, the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to develop the algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses the sample complexity of the problem, which is a topic of interest in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
